Appstore reviewers don't read the submission notes
text:
Dear HN,

I submit apps quite frequently. Since last year Apple requires accounts to be deleted. We've noticed that reviewers complain a lot on where to find this. We've put this in the user profile under the logout button.

To make it more clear we added where to do this in the notes of the submission, now even in capitals "HOW TO REMOVE YOUR ACCOUNT".

But many times we still get the question how to do this. Is there a better way to make this clear?

It's quite frustrating notes don't get read, even though the Apple submission explicitly asking for extensive submission notes.

Any advice to make submissions more easy?

title: Ash HN: What's the new “your data fits in RAM” for a new 8-socket Xeon Scalable?
text:

Ask HN: Prevent self doubt from affecting performance?
text:
Been at this big tech company for almost a year with about 5 years exp. Since start to present, I’ve just felt like I’m drowning. It seems like almost every topic I encounter requires me to deep dive for a few days just to get the fundamentals down, which is hard in an environment that moves at rapid pace. Compounding into this turbulent economy, my anxiety is pretty sky high.

How have you guys dealt with this in the past? I’d like to add that I’m pretty motivated and spend a great deal of time studying and reading, but the mix of pressure, lacking knowledge and anxiety is really killing me right now.
